{
  "texts": [
    "The approach to logicist AI-based on cognitive calculi is not restricted in any way to \"off the shelf \" logics but are instead created and specified for given purposes and applications in AI.",
    "However, all cognitive calculi include standard extensional logics (one or more of L 0, L 1, L 2, L 3, and standard natural-inference schemata for these extensional logics).",
    "C(t, P(a, t, φ) → K(a, t, φ))",
    "s, h, t, φ) B(h, t, B(s, t, φ)) [I 12 ] I(a, t, happens(action(a *, α), t ′)) P(a, t, happens(action(a *, α), t ′)) [I 13 ] B(a, t, φ) B(a, t, O(a, t, φ, χ)) O(a, t, φ, χ) K(a, t, I(a, t, χ)) [I 14 ]",
    "The following two framed boxes specify the additional signature and inference schemata for IDCEC, respectively."
  ]
}